channeldata.description: parse_type extends the parse module (opposite of string.format()) with the following features:   * build type converters for common use cases (enum/mapping, choice)   * build a type converter with a cardinality constraint (0..1, 0..*, 1..*) from the type converter with cardinality=1.   * compose a type converter from other type converters   * an extended parser that supports the CardinalityField naming schema and creates missing type variants (0..1, 0..*, 1..*) from the primary type converter dev_url: https://github.com/jenisys/parse_type
channeldata.summary: Simplifies to build parse types based on the parse module
